isDiscoveredUnitSame

public boolean isDiscoveredUnitSame(Unit unit1,
                                    Unit unit2)
Description copied from class: TopologyDiscoverer
Determines if two units are the "same" unit. Two units are the same if they would be represented by the same Unit in the same Topology. The units compared need not be in the same Topology.

Specified by:
isDiscoveredUnitSame in class TopologyDiscoverer
Parameters:
unit1 - one unit
unit2 - the other unit
Returns:
true if the units are the same unit; false if not or if not determinable
